cs.AR, cs.PF, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.PL

The paper discusses research on memory systems and graphics processing units (GPU), which are typically studied in the computer architecture (cs.AR) and performance (cs.PF) sub-categories. The paper also discusses issues related to managing resources and interference in multicore and heterogeneous systems, which fall under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses programmability and portability issues in GPUs, which are studied in the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
